 <sn><md>### Biography of Jesus Christ
---

![jesus](https://images.pexels.com/photos/51524/pexels-photo-51524.jpeg?auto=compress&amp;cs=tinysrgb&amp;fit=crop&amp;h=627&amp;w=1200)

**Jesus of Nazareth**, also known as **Jesus Christ**, is the central figure of Christianity, one of the most influential and widely followed religious traditions in human history. His life and teachings are the foundation of Christian faith, and he is also considered a prophet in Islam and an important teacher by many other spiritual traditions.

---

### 📜 Early Life

| Aspect        | Detail                                                                              |
| ------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Birth**     | Around 4–6 BCE, in Bethlehem (Judea, now Palestine/Israel)                          |
| **Parents**   | Mary (a virgin at the time, according to Christian belief) and Joseph (a carpenter) |
| **Ancestry**  | From the lineage of King David                                                      |
| **Residence** | Raised in Nazareth, Galilee                                                         |

* The **Gospels of Matthew and Luke** describe Jesus' birth as miraculous.
* He grew up in a Jewish household and learned Hebrew scriptures.

---

### 🧑‍🏫 Ministry

| Period | Around age 30 to 33 |
| ------ | ------------------- |

* Baptized by **John the Baptist** in the Jordan River.
* Preached about:

  * The **Kingdom of God**
  * **Love**, **forgiveness**, **humility**, and **compassion**
  * Challenged the religious elite and interpreted Jewish law with a new moral focus.

**Key events**:

* Performed miracles (healing the sick, feeding thousands, walking on water).
* Gathered **12 apostles** as close disciples.
* Delivered famous sermons (e.g., *Sermon on the Mount*).

---

### ✝️ Death and Resurrection

| Event            | Details                                                                                      |
| ---------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Crucifixion**  | Executed by the Romans under Pontius Pilate around 30–33 CE in Jerusalem                     |
| **Charges**      | Claimed to be “King of the Jews” – seen as a threat by both Roman and Jewish authorities     |
| **Burial**       | Laid in a tomb donated by Joseph of Arimathea                                                |
| **Resurrection** | Christians believe he rose from the dead on the third day (Easter) and appeared to followers |

---

### 🔄 Legacy

| Aspect            | Influence                                                                            |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Religion**      | Founder of Christianity                                                              |
| **Scripture**     | Life and teachings recorded in the New Testament Gospels (Matthew, Mark, Luke, John) |
| **Ethics**        | Central figure in discussions of morality, peace, justice, and love                  |
| **Global Impact** | Christianity became the world's largest religion with over 2 billion followers       |

---

### ✨ Titles and Roles

* **Christ / Messiah** – The “anointed one” (Greek: Christos, Hebrew: Mashiach)
* **Son of God** – Core belief in Christian doctrine
* **Rabbi / Teacher**
* **Savior / Redeemer**
* **The Word (Logos)** in the Gospel of John

---

### 🧾 Summary Points

* Born around 4–6 BCE in Bethlehem, raised in Nazareth.
* Began ministry around age 30, preaching love, justice, and the coming Kingdom of God.
